"""
Master timeline occurrences for the v2 dataset.

Conventions:
- IDs must be unique and >= 1_000_000.
- Years are integers. Use negative numbers for BCE.
- end_year is omitted (or equal to start_year) for singular occurrences.
- start_month/start_day, end_month/end_day, key_month/key_day are
  optional integers — set them where precise dates are known.
- date_uncertain=True adds a * to the displayed date.
- priorities is a dict {timeline_slug: priority_int}. Current scale 0-1_000_000.
- region_weights is a dict {region: int 1-10}, used by the master and
  arts-and-thoughts:main timelines for region-weighted ranking.
- first_zoom_out / second_zoom_out (optional) name the umbrella period(s)
  this sub-event rolls up to. The UI collapses sub-events into the umbrella
  at low zoom levels.

History:
- Sessions 1-7: build-up to 2,231 entries.
- Session 8 (2026-05-19): dedup + atomisation, 2,217 entries.
- Rollup work (2026-05-19): umbrellas added, 2,317 entries.
- Session 9 (2026-05-22): monarchy gaps, umbrella backfill, Cold War tagging,
  england-monarchs priority re-curation.
- Session 10 (2026-05-22, backfill 1/3): added precise month/day to high-
  priority post-1500 entries (Salt March, Chrysler Building, WW1/WW2,
  French Revolution, Cold War, etc.).
"""

